(41) ‘direct electronic access’ means an arrangement where a member or participant or client of a trading venue permits a
person to use its trading code so the person can electronically transmit orders relating to a financial instrument
directly to the trading venue and includes arrangements which involve the use by a person of the infrastructure of
the member or participant or client, or any connecting system provided by the member or participant or client, to
